summary:
Pentagon deployed 2,000 airborne troops to the Middle East for operational options as the Trump administration delivered a 15-point ceasefire proposal to Iran via Pakistan. Iran permitted non-hostile oil vessels through the Strait of Hormuz. This follows Iran's missile and drone launches at Israel and Gulf Arab states yesterday. The moves affect global energy security and regional war dynamics. Tehran response is awaited.

Israeli forces conducted strikes in southern Lebanon towns and a Palestinian refugee camp near Sidon, killing nine people including Lebanese civilians and refugees. Separately, Israel permitted displaced Palestinians to cross a bisecting military zone into northern Gaza after a hostage release impasse resolved, affecting hundreds of thousands of returnees and easing humanitarian access. In Europe, investigators probed attacks on Jewish schools and sites in multiple countries, with suspicions pointing to Iran, affecting Jewish community security.

In Sudan, army drone strikes hit a hospital in East Darfur, killing 64 people including children and medical staff and wounding 89 others, per WHO, affecting war-torn civilians. Rwanda-backed rebels overran Congolese troops and entered Goma, trapping over one million displaced people amid gunfire and shelling, threatening the aid hub. NATO launched its first coordinated response after a suspected sabotage severed a Baltic Sea cable, affecting alliance communications. A New Mexico jury fined Meta $375 million for child safety violations on Instagram and Facebook. SpaceX launched Crew-10 from Kennedy Space Center to retrieve NASA astronauts Butch Wilmore and Suni Williams, stuck on ISS since June. US-assisted Ecuador airstrike destroyed a dairy farm mistaken for a drug cartel camp. OpenAI discontinued its Sora AI video generator amid deepfake concerns."}
